## Common failure modes

- **Drift from the spec.** The implementation diverges from the PRD; the PRD is not updated. Fix by updating the PRD in the same pull request.
- **Silent skip.** A code path is added but no test covers it. Fix by writing the test before the code path lands.
- **Owner unclear.** A piece of work has no single owner; everyone assumes someone else is responsible. Fix by assigning a name in writing.
- **Plan without check-in.** A plan is written but never reviewed against reality. Fix by scheduling the review at the same time as the plan is written.
- **Decision without record.** A choice is made in a meeting; no one records it. Fix by writing the decision in the *Decision Log* before leaving the meeting.

